    "comment": "Rationale: Use of a well-documented specific blocker of this type of voltage gated calcium channel reduces evoked inhibitory postsynaptic currents and increased paired pulse ratios, implying a presynaptic origin.\n\n8/2/2018 Pim\n- The effect on Ca2+ is not shown directly in these experiments. However, CACNA1E is a known VGCC. The presynaptic action of CACNA1E inhibitor on ca2+-dependent SV release implies that CACNA1E is involved in 'voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium levels (GO:0099626)'.. Experimental description: Methods: Most experiments were done on transverse rat brain slices taken through the middle anterior portion of the nRT",
